#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.30:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Gahapativagga"
msgstr "3. Householders"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 30. Anuruddhamahāvitakkasutta → anuruddhasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Anuruddhamahāvitakkasutta"
msgstr "30. Anuruddha and the Great Thoughts"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.229"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati suṃsumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile "
"Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā anuruddho cetīsu viharati pācīnavaṃsadāye."
msgstr ""
"And at that time Venerable Anuruddha was staying in the land of the Cetīs in "
"the Eastern Bamboo Park."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmato anuruddhassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso "
"parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr "Then as Anuruddha was in private retreat this thought came to his mind:"

msgctxt "an8.30:1.4"
msgid "“appicchassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo mahicchassa;"
msgstr "“This teaching is for those of few wishes, not those of many wishes."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.5"
msgid "santuṭṭhassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asantuṭṭhassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the contented, not the discontented."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.6"
msgid "pavivittassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo saṅgaṇikārāmassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the secluded, not those who enjoy company."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.7"
msgid "āraddhavīriyassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo kusītassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the energetic, not the lazy."

#. VAR: upaṭṭhitassatissāyaṃ → upaṭṭhitasatissāyaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.30:1.8"
msgid "upaṭṭhitassatissāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo muṭṭhassatissa;"
msgstr "It’s for the mindful, not the unmindful."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.9"
msgid "samāhitassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asamāhitassa;"
msgstr "It’s for those with immersion, not those without immersion."

msgctxt "an8.30:1.10"
msgid "paññavato ayaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo duppaññassā”ti."
msgstr "It’s for the wise, not the witless.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmato anuruddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—"
"seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā "
"bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evamevaṃ—bhaggesu susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye "
"antarahito cetīsu pācīnavaṃsadāye āyasmato anuruddhassa sammukhe pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha knew what Anuruddha was thinking. As easily as a strong "
"person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the deer park at "
"Bhesakaḷā’s Wood in the land of the Bhaggas and reappeared in front of "
"Anurruddha in the Eastern Bamboo Park in the land of the Cetīs,"

msgctxt "an8.30:2.2"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "and sat on the seat spread out."

msgctxt "an8.30:2.3"
msgid "Āyasmāpi kho anuruddho bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "Anuruddha bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "an8.30:2.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:3.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, anuruddha."
msgstr "“Good, good, Anuruddha!"

# I prefer to gender the term mahapurisa, one of the few contexts where I elect for a gendered translation where BB uses a non-gendered one. Mahapurisa is a culturally potent term, comparable to the English “superman”. In its more worldly senses it is emphatically gendered, and I think it is significant to sustain this connection.
#. VAR: yaṃ taṃ mahāpurisavitakkaṃ → satta mahāpurisavitakke (pā1) 8D:1262
msgctxt "an8.30:3.2"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, yaṃ taṃ mahāpurisavitakkaṃ vitakkesi:"
msgstr "It’s good that you reflect on these thoughts of a great man:"

msgctxt "an8.30:3.3"
msgid "‘appicchassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo mahicchassa;"
msgstr "‘This teaching is for those of few wishes, not those of many wishes."

msgctxt "an8.30:3.4"
msgid "santuṭṭhassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asantuṭṭhassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the contented, not the discontented."

msgctxt "an8.30:3.5"
msgid "pavivittassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo saṅgaṇikārāmassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the secluded, not those who enjoy company."

msgctxt "an8.30:3.6"
msgid "āraddhavīriyassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo kusītassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the energetic, not the lazy."

msgctxt "an8.30:3.7"
msgid "upaṭṭhitassatissāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo muṭṭhassatissa;"
msgstr "It’s for the mindful, not the unmindful."

msgctxt "an8.30:3.8"
msgid "samāhitassāyaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asamāhitassa;"
msgstr "It’s for those with immersion, not those without immersion."

msgctxt "an8.30:3.9"
msgid "paññavato ayaṃ dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo duppaññassā’ti."
msgstr "It’s for the wise, not the witless.’"

msgctxt "an8.30:3.10"
msgid "Tena hi tvaṃ, anuruddha, imampi aṭṭhamaṃ mahāpurisavitakkaṃ vitakkehi:"
msgstr ""
"Well then, Anuruddha, you should also reflect on the following eighth "
"thought of a great man:"

msgctxt "an8.30:3.11"
msgid ""
"‘nippapañcārāmassāyaṃ dhammo nippapañcaratino, nāyaṃ dhammo papañcārāmassa "
"papañcaratino’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for those who don’t enjoy proliferating and don’t like to "
"proliferate, not for those who enjoy proliferating and like to proliferate.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.230"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, tato "
"tvaṃ, anuruddha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi "
"dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharissasi."
msgstr ""
"First you’ll reflect on these eight thoughts of a great man. Then whenever "
"you want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful "
"qualities, you’ll enter and remain in the first absorption, which has the "
"rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:5.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, tato "
"tvaṃ, anuruddha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi, vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ "
"sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharissasi."
msgstr ""
"You’ll enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified "
"mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, tato "
"tvaṃ, anuruddha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi, pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca "
"viharissasi sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedissasi yaṃ taṃ ariyā "
"ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharissasi."
msgstr ""
"You’ll enter and remain in the third absorption, where you’ll meditate with "
"equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which "
"the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, tato "
"tvaṃ, anuruddha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi, sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca "
"pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharissasi."
msgstr ""
"Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, you’ll "
"enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with "
"pure equanimity and mindfulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime ca aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, "
"imesañca catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhī bhavissasi akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, tato tuyhaṃ, anuruddha, "
"seyyathāpi nāma gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā nānārattānaṃ dussānaṃ "
"dussakaraṇḍako pūro;"
msgstr ""
"First you’ll reflect on these eight thoughts of a great man, and you’ll get "
"the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to "
"the higher mind—when you want, without trouble or difficulty. Then as you "
"live contented your rag robe will seem to you like a chest full of garments "
"of different colors seems to a householder or householder’s child."

msgctxt "an8.30:8.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ te paṃsukūlacīvaraṃ khāyissati santuṭṭhassa viharato ratiyā "
"aparitassāya phāsuvihārāya okkamanāya nibbānassa."
msgstr ""
"It will be for your enjoyment, relief, and comfort, and for alighting upon "
"extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.231"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:9.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime ca aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, "
"imesañca catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhī bhavissasi akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, tato tuyhaṃ, anuruddha, "
"seyyathāpi nāma gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā sālīnaṃ odano "
"vicitakāḷako anekasūpo anekabyañjano;"
msgstr ""
"As you live contented your scraps of alms-food will seem to you like boiled "
"fine rice with the dark grains picked out, served with many soups and sauces "
"seems to a householder or householder’s child."

msgctxt "an8.30:9.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ te piṇḍiyālopabhojanaṃ khāyissati santuṭṭhassa viharato ratiyā "
"aparitassāya phāsuvihārāya okkamanāya nibbānassa."
msgstr ""
"It will be for your enjoyment, relief, and comfort, and for alighting upon "
"extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:10.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime ca aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, "
"imesañca catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhī bhavissasi akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, tato tuyhaṃ, anuruddha, "
"seyyathāpi nāma gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā kūṭāgāraṃ ullittāvalittaṃ "
"nivātaṃ phusitaggaḷaṃ pihitavātapānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"As you live contented your lodging at the root of a tree will seem to you "
"like a bungalow, plastered inside and out, draft-free, with latches fastened "
"and windows shuttered seems to a householder or householder’s child."

msgctxt "an8.30:10.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ te rukkhamūlasenāsanaṃ khāyissati santuṭṭhassa viharato ratiyā "
"aparitassāya phāsuvihārāya okkamanāya nibbānassa."
msgstr ""
"It will be for your enjoyment, relief, and comfort, and for alighting upon "
"extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo → kādali … paccattharaṇo (bj)
msgctxt "an8.30:11.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime ca aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, "
"imesañca catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhī bhavissasi akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, tato tuyhaṃ, anuruddha, "
"seyyathāpi nāma gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā pallaṅko gonakatthato "
"paṭikatthato paṭalikatthato kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo sauttaracchado "
"ubhatolohitakūpadhāno;"
msgstr ""
"As you live contented your lodging at the root of a tree will seem to you "
"like a couch spread with woolen covers—shag-piled, pure white, or "
"embroidered with flowers—and spread with a fine deer hide, with a canopy "
"above and red pillows at both ends seems to a householder or householder’s "
"child."

msgctxt "an8.30:11.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ te tiṇasanthārakasayanāsanaṃ khāyissati santuṭṭhassa viharato "
"ratiyā aparitassāya phāsuvihārāya okkamanāya nibbānassa."
msgstr ""
"It will be for your enjoyment, relief, and comfort, and for alighting upon "
"extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.232"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:12.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho tvaṃ, anuruddha, ime ca aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakke vitakkessasi, "
"imesañca catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhī bhavissasi akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, tato tuyhaṃ, anuruddha, "
"seyyathāpi nāma gahapatissa vā gahapatiputtassa vā nānābhesajjāni, "
"seyyathidaṃ—sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"As you live contented your fermented urine as medicine will seem to you like "
"various medicines—ghee, butter, oil, honey, molasses, and salt—seem to a "
"householder or householder’s child."

msgctxt "an8.30:12.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ te pūtimuttabhesajjaṃ khāyissati santuṭṭhassa viharato ratiyā "
"aparitassāya phāsuvihārāya okkamanāya nibbānassa."
msgstr ""
"It will be for your enjoyment, relief, and comfort, and for alighting upon "
"extinguishment."

# This passage is a good example showing that “therefore” is not suited as translation for the “tena hi” idiom. Despite the instrumental, there’s no logical connection implied, merely a loose transition, for which we use “so” in English.
msgctxt "an8.30:12.3"
msgid ""
"Tena hi tvaṃ, anuruddha, āyatikampi vassāvāsaṃ idheva cetīsu pācīnavaṃsadāye "
"vihareyyāsī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Well then, Anuruddha, for the next rainy season residence you should stay "
"right here in the land of the Cetīs in the Eastern Bamboo Park.”"

msgctxt "an8.30:12.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā anuruddho bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Anuruddha replied."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.233"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ iminā ovādena ovaditvā—seyyathāpi "
"nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ "
"samiñjeyya; evamevaṃ—cetīsu pācīnavaṃsadāye antarahito bhaggesu susumāragire "
"bhesakaḷāvane migadāye pāturahosīti."
msgstr ""
"After advising Anuruddha like this, the Buddha—as easily as a strong person "
"would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Eastern Bamboo Park in "
"the land of the Cetīs and reappeared in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood in "
"the land of the Bhaggas."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.2"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "He sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "an8.30:13.3"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an8.30:13.4"
msgid "“aṭṭha kho, bhikkhave, mahāpurisavitakke desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you the eight thoughts of a great man. Listen …"

msgctxt "an8.30:13.5"
msgid "katame ca, bhikkhave, aṭṭha mahāpurisavitakkā?"
msgstr "And what are the eight thoughts of a great man?"

msgctxt "an8.30:13.6"
msgid "Appicchassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo mahicchassa;"
msgstr "This teaching is for those of few wishes, not those of many wishes."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.7"
msgid "santuṭṭhassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asantuṭṭhassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the contented, not the discontented."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.8"
msgid "pavivittassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo saṅgaṇikārāmassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the secluded, not those who enjoy company."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.9"
msgid "āraddhavīriyassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo kusītassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the energetic, not the lazy."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.10"
msgid "upaṭṭhitassatissāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo muṭṭhassatissa;"
msgstr "It’s for the mindful, not the unmindful."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.11"
msgid "samāhitassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asamāhitassa;"
msgstr "It’s for those with immersion, not those without immersion."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.12"
msgid "paññavato ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo duppaññassa;"
msgstr "It’s for the wise, not the witless."

msgctxt "an8.30:13.13"
msgid ""
"nippapañcārāmassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo nippapañcaratino, nāyaṃ dhammo "
"papañcārāmassa papañcaratino."
msgstr ""
"It’s for those who don’t enjoy proliferating and don’t like to proliferate, "
"not for those who enjoy proliferating and like to proliferate."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:14.1"
msgid "‘Appicchassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo mahicchassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for those of few wishes, not those of many wishes.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:14.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:14.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appiccho samāno ‘appicchoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na "
"icchati, santuṭṭho samāno ‘santuṭṭhoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na icchati, pavivitto "
"samāno ‘pavivittoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na icchati, āraddhavīriyo samāno ‘"
"āraddhavīriyoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na icchati, upaṭṭhitassati samāno ‘"
"upaṭṭhitassatīti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na icchati, samāhito samāno ‘samāhitoti maṃ "
"jāneyyun’ti na icchati, paññavā samāno ‘paññavāti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na "
"icchati, nippapañcārāmo samāno ‘nippapañcārāmoti maṃ jāneyyun’ti na icchati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with few wishes doesn’t wish: ‘May they know me as having few "
"wishes!’ When contented, they don’t wish: ‘May they know me as contented!’ "
"When secluded, they don’t wish: ‘May they know me as secluded!’ When "
"energetic, they don’t wish: ‘May they know me as energetic!’ When mindful, "
"they don’t wish: ‘May they know me as mindful!’ When immersed, they don’t "
"wish: ‘May they know me as immersed!’ When wise, they don’t wish: ‘May they "
"know me as wise!’ When not enjoying proliferation, they don’t wish: ‘May "
"they know me as one who doesn’t enjoy proliferating!’"

msgctxt "an8.30:14.4"
msgid "‘Appicchassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo mahicchassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for those of few wishes, not those of many wishes.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:14.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (1)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:15.1"
msgid ""
"‘Santuṭṭhassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asantuṭṭhassā’ti, iti kho "
"panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for the contented, not the discontented.’ That’s what I "
"said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:15.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti "
"itarītaracīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant who’s content with any kind of robes, alms-food, "
"lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "an8.30:15.3"
msgid "‘Santuṭṭhassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asantuṭṭhassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the contented, not the discontented.’"

msgctxt "an8.30:15.4"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (2)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.234"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:16.1"
msgid ""
"‘Pavivittassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo saṅgaṇikārāmassā’ti, iti "
"kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for the secluded, not those who enjoy company.’ That’s "
"what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:16.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pavivittassa viharato bhavanti upasaṅkamitāro "
"bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo rājāno rājamahāmattā titthiyā "
"titthiyasāvakā."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant who lives secluded. But monks, nuns, laymen, laywomen, "
"rulers and their ministers, founders of religious sects, and their disciples "
"go to visit them."

#. VAR: kattā → pavattā (mr)
msgctxt "an8.30:16.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra bhikkhu vivekaninnena cittena vivekapoṇena vivekapabbhārena "
"vivekaṭṭhena nekkhammābhiratena aññadatthu uyyojanikapaṭisaṃyuttaṃyeva "
"kathaṃ kattā hoti."
msgstr ""
"With a mind slanting, sloping, and inclining to seclusion, withdrawn, and "
"loving renunciation, that mendicant invariably gives each of them a talk "
"emphasizing the topic of dismissal."

msgctxt "an8.30:16.4"
msgid "‘Pavivittassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo saṅgaṇikārāmassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the secluded, not those who enjoy company.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:16.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (3)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:17.1"
msgid ""
"‘Āraddhavīriyassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo kusītassā’ti, iti kho "
"panetaṃ vuttaṃ, kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for the energetic, not the lazy.’ That’s what I said, but "
"why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:17.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant who lives with energy roused up for giving up "
"unskillful qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, "
"staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful "
"qualities."

msgctxt "an8.30:17.3"
msgid "‘Āraddhavīriyassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo kusītassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the energetic, not the lazy.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:17.4"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (4)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:18.1"
msgid ""
"‘Upaṭṭhitassatissāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo muṭṭhassatissā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the mindful, not the unmindful.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:18.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:18.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satimā hoti paramena satinepakkena samannāgato, "
"cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi saritā anussaritā."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant who’s mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and "
"alertness, and can remember and recall what was said and done long ago."

msgctxt "an8.30:18.4"
msgid ""
"‘Upaṭṭhitassatissāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo, muṭṭhassatissā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the mindful, not the unmindful.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:18.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (5)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:19.1"
msgid "‘Samāhitassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asamāhitassā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for those with immersion, not those without immersion.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:19.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:19.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded "
"from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … "
"second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption."

msgctxt "an8.30:19.4"
msgid "‘Samāhitassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo asamāhitassā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for those with immersion, not those without immersion.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:19.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (6)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:20.1"
msgid "‘Paññavato ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo duppaññassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the wise, not the witless.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:20.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:20.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato "
"ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant who’s wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing "
"away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of "
"suffering."

msgctxt "an8.30:20.4"
msgid "‘Paññavato ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nāyaṃ dhammo duppaññassā’ti, "
msgstr "‘This teaching is for the wise, not the witless.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:20.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. (7)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.235"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:21.1"
msgid ""
"‘Nippapañcārāmassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo nippapañcaratino, nāyaṃ dhammo "
"papañcārāmassa papañcaratino’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for those who don’t enjoy proliferating and don’t like to "
"proliferate, not for those who enjoy proliferating and like to proliferate.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:21.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?"
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it?"

msgctxt "an8.30:21.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno papañcanirodhe cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati "
"santiṭṭhati vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"It’s for a mendicant whose mind is eager, confident, settled, and decided "
"regarding the cessation of proliferation."

msgctxt "an8.30:21.4"
msgid ""
"‘Nippapañcārāmassāyaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammo, nippapañcaratino, nāyaṃ dhammo "
"papañcārāmassa papañcaratino’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘This teaching is for those who don’t enjoy proliferating and don’t like to "
"proliferate, not for those who enjoy proliferating and like to proliferate.’ "

msgctxt "an8.30:21.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti. (8)"
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:22.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho āyatikampi vassāvāsaṃ tattheva cetīsu "
"pācīnavaṃsadāye vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Anuruddha stayed the next rainy season residence right there in the "
"land of the Cetīs in the Eastern Bamboo Park."

msgctxt "an8.30:22.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto "
"nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, "
"tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"And Anuruddha, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon "
"realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life. He "
"lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which people from "
"good families rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "an8.30:22.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "an8.30:22.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā anuruddho arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Anuruddha became one of the perfected."

msgctxt "an8.30:22.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho arahattappatto tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr "And on the occasion of attaining perfection he recited these verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:23.1"
msgid "“Mama saṅkappamaññāya,"
msgstr "“Knowing my thoughts,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:23.2"
msgid "satthā loke anuttaro;"
msgstr "the supreme Teacher in the world"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:23.3"
msgid "Manomayena kāyena,"
msgstr "came to me in a mind-made body,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:23.4"
msgid "iddhiyā upasaṅkami."
msgstr "using his psychic power."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:24.1"
msgid "Yathā me ahu saṅkappo,"
msgstr "He taught me more"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:24.2"
msgid "tato uttari desayi;"
msgstr "than I had thought of."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:24.3"
msgid "Nippapañcarato buddho,"
msgstr "The Buddha who loves non-proliferation"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:24.4"
msgid "nippapañcaṃ adesayi."
msgstr "taught me non-proliferation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:25.1"
msgid "Tassāhaṃ dhammamaññāya,"
msgstr "Understanding that teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:25.2"
msgid "vihāsiṃ sāsane rato;"
msgstr "I happily followed his instructions."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:25.3"
msgid "Tisso vijjā anuppattā,"
msgstr "I’ve attained the three knowledges,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:25.4"
msgid "kataṃ buddhassa sāsanan”ti."
msgstr "and have fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.30:25.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.30:25.6"
msgid "Gahapativaggo tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "an8.30:26.1"
msgid "Dve uggā dve ca hatthakā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:26.2"
msgid "mahānāmena jīvako;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:26.3"
msgid "Dve balā akkhaṇā vuttā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.30:26.4"
msgid "anuruddhena te dasāti."
msgstr ""
